This paper deals with data privacy protection in visual classification tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a method that modifies the original dataset to protect privacy, which could fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. The method also involves deep neural networks (DNNs), indicating that it could be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the experiments are conducted on image datasets, which suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
